<Link id="l00262" /><CodeLine lineNumber="262"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class can be used for tracking most instruction setters.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="263"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The two template arguments are:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="264"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - GetterFn: The getter member function pointer (e.g., &#96;&amp;Foo::get&#96;)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="265"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - SetterFn: The setter member function pointer (e.g., &#96;&amp;Foo::set&#96;)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="266"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Upon construction, it saves a copy of the original value by calling the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="267"><Highlight kind="comment">/// getter function. Revert sets the value back to the one saved, using the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><Highlight kind="comment">/// setter function provided.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Example:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271"><Highlight kind="comment">///  Tracker.track(std::make&#95;unique&lt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="272"><Highlight kind="comment">///                GenericSetter&lt;&amp;FooInst::get, &amp;FooInst::set&gt;&gt;(I, Tracker));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;auto GetterFn, auto SetterFn&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
